<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Weed2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Weed,</orth> subst. a useless or noxious herb: <cit><quote>they bid thee crop a w., thou pluckest a flower,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 946" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 946</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>no grass, herb, leaf or w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 946" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 946</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>the basest w. outbraves his dignity,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 94.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 94, 12</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 1, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 67</bibl>. Plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 281" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 281</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. luc 281" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 281</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 69.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 69, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.94.14" default="NO" valid="yes">94, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.124.4" default="NO" valid="yes">124, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 38</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 6, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 13</bibl> <cit><quote>(small herbs have grace, great --s do grow apace).</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.13" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 13</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 109</bibl> (<emph>as --s before a vessel under sail;</emph> i. e. water-plants). <bibl n="shak. rom 2.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.268" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 268</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.151" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.173" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 173</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 4, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 4, 3</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.390" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 390</bibl>. Peculiar passage: <cit><quote>the needful bits and curbs to headstrong --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 3, 20</bibl></cit> (Collier: '<emph>weed</emph> is a term still commonly applied to an ill-conditioned horse.' Emendations proposed: <emph>steeds</emph> or <emph>wills</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>